Module kivakit.service.registry
Package com.telenav.kivakit.service.registry

Class Service

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.service.registry.Service
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AsString, java.lang.Comparable<Service>
    public class Service
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Service>, AsString
    A logical service of a particular type that can be registered by an application with a local or network service registry, and subsequently discovered by client registry searches.

    Service Registration and Expiration

    A service of some ServiceType, with ServiceMetadata describing its function, may be registered by an Application in order to bind it to an unused port on the local host and make it discoverable by clients. When registered and bound, a service is visible within a particular Scope so long as the service renews its lease with the registry. If the lease expires, the service is removed from the registry. Lease renewal is handled automatically for applications that register a service using the service registration client.

    Service Discovery

    Registered services can be discovered using a service registration client, which communicates using a REST protocol with the registry. The criteria that are used for service discovery is detailed in ServiceRegistryClient.

    Service Properties

    A service has the following properties:

    • application() - Identifies the application registering the service
    • scope() - The scope where the service is visible
    • metadata() - Metadata describing the service
    • type() - Service type identifier for use in searching for services
    • port() - The port that the service is bound to or UNBOUND
    • renewedAt() - The most recent service lease renewal time
    • health() - Information about the health of the server running the service
